Package: nilHMM
Title: Duration-Aware HMM Ancestry Caller for NIL Sequencing Data
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R:
    person("Fausto", "Rodriguez Zapata", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "thegemmalab@ncsu.edu")
Description: A unified R + Rcpp reimplementation of the nilHMM ancestry-calling
    family for Near-Isogenic Lines from sequencing data. A single
    duration-aware 3-state (REF/HET/ALT) HMM engine with swappable emission
    models (count / gt) and duration layers (geometric / rigidity / hsmm)
    expresses a family of named callers: nnil (Holland's nNIL), rtiger (a
    Julia-free RTIGER port), binhmm (bin/cluster), atlas (GOOGA thresholds),
    lbimpute (an LB-Impute port for very low coverage), and fsfhap (a TASSEL
    FSFHap port for full-sib families). The package is data-agnostic: functions
    take (data, params) and return calls in a common segment schema; pipeline
    scripts own paths and sample lists.
